TapJoy
-
Provided by: TapJoy,
Inc.
-
Collected
information: I - Device identifiers (a device identifier is a string of numbers
and letters unique to your smartphone or tablet assigned by the manufacturer or
platform provider), such as: a) Advertising identifier – this is a resettable
identifier for advertising use, such as Google Android Advertising ID (GAAID),
for Android devices, and ID for Advertisers (IDFA), for iOS devices; b)
Publishers of Android apps have the option of sending other identifiers, such
as Google Android ID or MAC address, for use as a fallback identifier or for
analytics use; c) The publisher’s user identifier: II - Information about the
device itself, including: a) Whether it is a smartphone or tablet; b) What
operating system and version it uses (example: iOS, version 11.0); c) Whether
the device’s “opt-out” options related to advertising have been enabled; d)
Model and manufacturer (example: Apple iPhone X, Samsung Galaxy S8); e) Screen
size, screen density, and other information relevant to ad formatting and
display; III - Information about the internet connection used to access our
services, including: a) Mobile carrier; b) Network provider; c) Whether the
network type is wifi or cellular; d) IP address; e) Timestamp and duration
(when the device connected to our services and how long the connection lasted,
for a given session); IV - Information about the app used to access our
services and your use of it, and about our SDK, including: a) Which version of
the app is being used ,and which version of our SDK is integrated in the app;
b) API key (identifier for application); c) How frequently and for how long you
use the app, and, at the publisher’s option, information about what level of
the game you’re on and your in-app purchases; d) If the publisher uses
mediation to connect with ad networks, it may opt to send or enable collection
of parameters related to mediation services; e) Signals relating to eligibility
for behavioral advertising; V - Location-related information - We do not
request or receive precise (sometimes referred to as “lat-long”) geolocation
data; we infer the perceived general location of the device based on: a) The IP
address used to access our services b) Location-related device settings, such
as the device’s country code, language setting, and time zone; VI - Information
relating to campaign content - We collect information about the campaign
content you view, such as: a) What the campaign content is about; b) What type
of campaign content it is (example: video); c) The reward offered in exchange
for your engagement with the campaign content; d) Which placement is involved
(meaning, where and how the campaign content is displayed in the mobile app
where you accessed it); e) Whether you respond to the campaign content’s “call
to action” - for example, did you click through to the advertiser’s website? –
or complete its requirements (examples: watching a 30-second video; making a
purchase); f) Market research information; VII - Responses to market research
surveys accessed through our platform are voluntary and opt-in. Responses
voluntarily provided by you may include: a) Demographic information (such as
age, household income, gender, highest education completed, household
composition); b) General location (such as postal code, or city and state); c)
Other information you voluntarily provide, which may include product
preferences and opinions, employment status, marital status, veteran status,
health information, race or ethnic origin, political opinions, membership
information, sexual orientation, religious beliefs - in each case, subject to
applicable law.
-
Privacy Policy:
https://www.tapjoy.com/legal/players/privacy-policy/
